channel.title: I had this fucked up dream
channel.description:
And I thought I would share it with everyone.
http://pastebin.com/85qS0wrK
[quote="Thug-life"]the forum.. [quote]These events will probably be a little less than what I had dreamt them to be since... yano, you start forgetting the dream the more you're not dreaming about them haha.
Anyhow, Dream started out as being in a house I've never been in or near, nothing I can quite remember. I think we were just moving in because I was bringing my cat there for what felt like the first time. This dear/kangaroo thing (Mainly saw the face for the most part, and its neck was quite lanky and long) started fuckin' with my cat and biting it, etc. For some reason the cat was just sitting around, but whatever. I ran over to this (From here on out, "creature"), and just started beating the shit out of it. I could feel it biting me, but they were only nibbles. It didn't seem like I did any damage to it yet, from what it looked like. I brought it into the house I was figuring out how to choke it (Apparently in dreams, the neck isn't the first thing you look at). Like I said, its neck was very skinny. It didn't even seem like it had bone in it (Just describing LoL). It was like.. larger than a hose, but the same concept LoL. Eventually, it ended up with me putting both knees on its neck. I was imagining the look on its face, how it was scared, etc D: It was gasping for air and all that jazz as well. At one point, my mother and brother walk in and they hadn't noticed what I was doing, so it seemed. I didn't want them to, so I was like.. "Keep walking." in a kinda semi-urgent way. "What?" "KEEP FUCKING WALKING!" Anyhow, I'm still choking this thing; wouldn't die, wouldn't die, wouldn't die. I eventually ended up putting a palm on the back of its neck and then it's chin and twisting its head past the point of looking back at me. Again, I could see the fear in it's eyes D: It was pretty much dead by this point. It actually managed to twitch a little bit.. More like the leftover fight in it made it just.. shake midly. There was orange stuff on the wall, instead of red blood D: It was like the sauce in canned raviolis from Shoprite. Whatever.. Anyhow, I went and got two trash bags. I stuffed it head first in the one, sealed it up, then put the open end in the bottom of the other trash bag.
Then I woke up.[/quote][/quote]
